@database "Extention.guide"
@width 80
@node main "Extention List Contents"

       @{b} Amiga Guide Extention Lister

          By Robbie Wegner. V1.7@{ub}

    Click here to @{"Search" system "run S:ExtListersearch Sample2.Guide.2 "} for string.

 List of @{" Amiga Guides " link " .Guide 10000"} @{"  Documents   " link " .Doc 10010"} @{"     Text     " link " .txt 10020"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 0"} SYS:Documents/

 List of @{"  HAM 8 Pics  " link " .Ham8 10031"} @{"   IFF Pics   " link " .IFF 10041"} @{"   GIF Pics   " link " .gif 10051"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 1"} STORAGE:PICTURES/Raytrace/

 List of @{"  LHA Files   " link " .LHA 10062"} @{" LHA ReadMes  " link " .readme 10072"}  @{"DirAll" link "All 2"} SPARE:LHA/SYS/WBStartup/


 @{b}List of@{ub} @{"THE WORKS!" link "Theworks"}

  INFO-
   This is a sample "Seperate Extentions each Directory selection" guide,
 generated by the ExtLister script.

    It has the Directory "ALL" and "THE WORKS!" list options on and customised
  button names in the contents window. The Works list is not that useful
  in this type of Guide, but is there if you want it. Of more use is the
  Directory ALL list.

    Some of the Extentions have the Extra Tool Button selected and some
  don't. The LHA one has the standard button set to the ExtLHA-View script and
  the UN-Pack button is set to the ExtLHA-X extract script that both come with
  the package (they are in the S directory in the package). (There are two LZX
  ones there as well.) 

   The script will find the longest extention name or Customised Button name
 and make all of the buttons in the contents window the same size and
 centered to make the front page look neater.

  This example lists the individual extention files in seperate lists, however,
 you can search for multiple extentions for one list, using the standard
 Dos OR switch, though I have not given an example here. For instance-

  (.IFF|.ILBM|.HAM)  or (.LHA|.LZH) would be a usefull one.

  This is entered in the manual entry for the extention type to search for,
 at the guides creation.

 NOTE: The search function will not work until the ExtListerSearch file is put
 in the S: directory and AskEnv is put in the C: directory.

  You cannot load the actual files listed, cos they are on my machine :^) 
@endnode
